FBIS3-51106 "drlat009_m_94003" FBIS-LAT-94-009 Document Type:Daily Report 13 Jan 1994 Brazil Lula Denies Charges; PT To Accuse Maluf, Quercia, Others PY1201121294 Rio de Janeiro O GLOBO in Portuguese 11 Jan 94 p 1 PY1201121294 Rio de Janeiro O GLOBO Language: Portuguese Article Type:BFN [Text] PT [Workers Party] President Luis Inacio Lula da Silva stated on 10 January that a political campaign exists to defame the party. He indicated that the death of labor leader Osvaldo Cruz Jr. is being used by his adversaries due to his good conduct in the investigation. Lula also stated that the PT is going to bring charges against [Sao Paulo City] Mayor Paulo Maluf (PPR [Progressive Renewal Party]); Union Force President Luiz Antonio de Medeiros; Justice Minister Mauricio Correa; Nelson Guimaraes, the police commissioner in charge of the case; and probably former [Sao Paulo State] Governor Orestes Quercia, who have accused the PT of being involved in Osvaldo Cruz Jr.'s death.
